  "description": "Karl Gustaf Lund was a Swedish Chief Engineer born on July 22, 1893, in Hille, Gävleborg County. He was the first son of Ferdinand L., a factory worker, and Maria Andersson. Karl married Sigrid Johansson in 1936, and they had two children named Ingvar (born 1938) and Lennart (born 1942). Karl had a bachelor's degree in engineering from the KTH Royal Institute of Technology. He worked as a chemist at Strömsnäs Järnverks A-B, Westinghouse Electric & Manuf. Co., and A-B Iggesunds Bruk. Later, Karl became the site manager at Gunnebo Bruks Nya A-B, Varbergsverket, where he served since 1931. He was also actively involved in various organizations, including the Municipal Finance Committee, Varbergs Sparbank, Varbergs Air Defense Association, Varbergs Right Society, Railway Health Insurance Fund, and Plant's Society for Small Bird Friends. Karl had hobbies such as hunting and fishing."
